{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, each sample x n follows a circularly symmetric complex Gaussian distribution, such that x n ∼ CN (0, σ 2 x0), when bit 0 is transmitted, and x n ∼ CN (0, σ 2 x1), when bit 1 is transmitted.",
    "According to (7), to obtain the BEP, we first need to determine the statistics of the estimated sample varianceσ2 x|i,h = 1 N N n=1 |x n|i,h | 2, where x n|i,h is the conditional random variable of x n given h and that s i, i ∈ {0, 1} was transmitted, such that x n|i,h ∼ CN (0, σ 2 xi).",
    "However, for the sake of conciseness, we use σ2x andx n henceforth.",
    "Since |x n | 2 ∼ Exp 1 σ 2 x i, it follows that S ≜ N n=1 |x n | 2 is the sum of N independent exponential random variables with a common rate parameter 1/σ 2 xi, implying that S ∼ G(N, σ 2 xi) and consequently σ2 x ∼ G N, σ 2 xi /N.",
    "For convenience, let Z ≜ 2N σ2x /σ 2 xi."
  ]
}